The morphological characterization was done using scanning electron microscopy (EVO LS10 STEM) equipped with EDS X-ray microanalyzer. The photocurrent–voltage measurements were carried out using a VersaSTAT3 potentiostat (Princeton Applied Research) running cyclic voltammetry with a scan rate of 50 mV∙ s−1. A Honle solar simulator 400, with an AM 1.5G spectrum (100 mW/cm2) was used to simulate sunlight for irradiating the cells. The PCE (η) was calculated using the equationη=PmPi×100%=Jm·VmPi×100%.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
